abstract = {Vending machines are commonly observed in many regions across the globe, offering a convenient and round-the-clock means of acquiring commodities. Nevertheless, the accessibility of vending machines in Somalia is limited, and the majority of establishments, including pharmacies, do not operate round-the-clock. This issue might provide a challenge for those who require the acquisition of vital items of value, such as beverages or medication, beyond the typical operating hours of businesses. In response to this issue, a novel automated vending machine has been devised, leveraging Internet of Things (IoT) technology, enabling uninterrupted operation throughout the week, and encompassing all hours of the day. The machine is outfitted with a payment mechanism that accommodates the EVC-Plus mobile payment platform, which has extensive usage in Somalia. The machine has the potential to be used in a diverse range of public settings, including educational institutions, healthcare facilities, sports arenas, and various other communal spaces. The vending machine has the capacity to facilitate the sale of a diverse range of products, including beverages, snacks, writing implements, and pharmaceuticals. The machine operates on IoT technology, enabling it to establish connectivity with the Internet and facilitating remote monitoring and control capabilities. The machine is operated using a software program that enables users to engage with it using a touchscreen interface. Additionally, the application offers up-to-date information regarding the inventory and status of the machine.}
